a company that is not a joint-stock company as in section 355 defined shall not register in pursuance of this section as a
company limited by shares;
(d)) a company shall not register in pursuance of this section without the assent of a majority of such of its members as are
present in person or by proxy, on cases where proxies are allowed by the articles at a general meeting summoned for the
purpose;

where a company not having the liability of its members limited by Act of Parliament is about to register as a limited
company, the molarity required to assent as mentioned it clause (d) shall consist of not less than three-fourths of the
members present in person or by proxy at the meeting;
